OL,3,CJohn Stones to leave Manchester City
OL,4,Cat the end of the season
OL,6,FCity paid tribute to Stones on their
OL,7,Fwebsite, saying: "The 31-year-old's
OL,8,Fhuge contribution across the most
OL,9,Fsustained and successful era in the
OL,10,Fclub's history stands without question.
OL,12,F"Now the club and all of our
OL,13,Fsupporters will take the time to
OL,14,Fdeliver a fitting tribute and farewell
OL,15,Fto a superb servant of Manchester City
OL,16,Fat the end of the season."
OL,18,FStones was part of City's treble-
OL,19,Fwinning team in 2022/23 which won the
OL,20,FPremier League, Champions League and
OL,21,FFA Cup in the same season.
OL,26,@oD@ROUtD@AOUxD@ZO]
